OL,3,CFamily's renewed calls for assisted
OL,4,Cdying ahead of parliamentary debate
OL,6,FNext week, a bill which would allow
OL,7,Fterminally ill adults to lawfully end
OL,8,Ftheir own lives will be debated in the
OL,9,FHouse of Lords.
OL,11,FCurrently, under UK law it is illegal
OL,12,Fto assist someone's death, including
OL,13,Faiding someone to leave the UK in
OL,14,Forder to visit an assisted dying
OL,15,Fclinic.
OL,17,FNaomi told ITV Tyne Tees that the UK
OL,18,Flaw took her father's right to choose
OL,19,Fhow and where to die away from him.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G2/8
