OL,3,CFamily's renewed calls for assisted
OL,4,Cdying ahead of parliamentary debate
OL,6,FThe exact details of the controversial
OL,7,Fassisted dying bill are not yet fully
OL,8,Fknown but it is understood that it
OL,9,Fwill allow terminally ill patients who
OL,10,Fhave six months or less to live the
OL,11,Fright to medical help to end their
OL,12,Flife.
OL,14,FHowever, opponents to the bill worry
OL,15,Fit poses serious risks to vulnerable
OL,16,Fpeople.
OL,18,FThe former Paralympic gold medalist
OL,19,Fand a crossbencher in the House of
OL,20,FLords, Baroness Tanni Grey Thompson
OL,21,Fopposes the bill.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G5/8
